# gjc-relay runtime config (NON-SECRET). Mode 0600 by convention.
# The relay holds NO Discord/GitHub token in env — the bot token arrives per-request
# in the Authorization header from clawhip and is forwarded, never stored or logged.
RELAY_BIND={{RELAY_BIND}}
RELAY_DESIGN_SYSTEM={{HOME}}/.gjc-relay/design-system.json
# Managed work-item state lives here (registry / anchor ids). The relay defaults to
# this path; provisioning the directory is bootstrap's job (mode 0700 by convention).
RELAY_STATE_DIR={{HOME}}/.gjc-relay/state
# Out-of-band alert channel (#gjc-approvals) for dlq-watch.sh/alert.sh — consumed
# via EnvironmentFile= by their units. Numeric ID lives only in rendered files.
GJC_ALERT_CHANNEL={{CH_GJC_APPROVALS}}
# --- v2 managed work-item plumbing (appended by render.sh; numeric IDs stay out of
# tracked templates). RELAY_MANAGED_RATE is always emitted; RELAY_WORKITEM_CHANNELS is
# emitted empty by default => WorkitemChannels::None => the managed path is fully OFF
# and the relay behaves byte-identically to v1. Any RELAY_DEBOUNCE_SECS__<cid> lines are
# emitted only when [relay.debounce] pins a channel.
